news.title: NBCC auctions Amrapali flats worth Rs 7,000 crore to three developers
news.para: After the Uttar Pradesh government allowed NBCC to develop additional flats in the project, it estimated to generate an additional Rs 14,000 crore, which would have helped timely completion of stuck projects.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC to work with SRA, builders to redevelop Worli slums
news.para: The plan, arguably the first of its kind, envisages 12 acres of prime Govt and BMC land on the Worli sea face abutting the Coastal Road to be handed over to a consortium of city-based builders.

news.title: Telangana government launches slot booking system for property registrations
news.para: Revenue and registration minister Ponguleti Srinivas Reddy said slot booking started on a pilot basis at 22 sub-registrar offices, and the system would be extended to the entire state based on the outcome of the result.

news.title: Mumbai: Government approves 256 acres of salt pan land for Dharavi redevelopment project
news.para: DRP CEO SVR Srinivas said that these parcels had been officially decommissioned years ago and that no salt manufacturing had happened there for nearly a decade.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP orders developer to restore society's boundary wall & address safety concerns
news.para: Subsequently, a hearing was held on March 26, in which RWA of the society raised concerns over encroachments that could put residents' security at risk.

news.title: Telangana RERA halts Jayathri Infrastructure's project after multiple complaints
news.para: The complainants, including Sree Vatsala and others, later formed Jaya Diamonds Welfare Association and jointly filed a complaint, which became the basis for the proceedings.

news.title: Homebuyers in Noida protest against long delay in Jaypee Infratech projects
news.para: This was the first such protest against Suraksha, the resolution applicant that took over Jaypee Infratech Ltd (JIL) last May after a long-winded legal process.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA mandates prominent display of registration details in housing advertisements
news.para: The circular, issued on April 8, requires all housing advertisements to feature MahaRERA registration number, website address and project-specific QR code in a font size equal to or larger than the project's contact information.

news.title: Lulu International Shopping Malls acquires Manjeera Mall in Hyderabad
news.para: Currently, Lulu International is running its Hyderabad operations through Manjeera Mall on a lease basis. The NCLT order enables the tenant, Lulu, to become the owner of Manjeera Mall.

news.title: US citizens pay highest prices for Spanish property
news.para: While Spanish house prices are generally lower than in wealthier central and northern Europe, they jumped 11% last year, the second-biggest rise in the European Union after neighbouring Portugal, Eurostat data showed.

news.title: Britain's housing market suffers after end of tax incentives: Survey
news.para: The Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors' measure of new buyer enquiries fell to its lowest since September 2023 at a net balance of -32 in March, down for -16 in February.

news.title: NGT forms committee to probe illegal sand mining in Sundargarh
news.para: The committee includes senior scientists from the Odisha State Pollution Control Board (OSPCB) and State Environment Impact Assessment Authority (SEIAA), and the district collector or his representative.

news.title: Gurugram: NGT directs Haryana government to halt illegal mining in forest area till August 7
news.para: The NGT’s intervention follows a report by The Times of India that highlighted the auction of protected Aravali land for mining in Rajawas.

news.title: Centre notifies rules to manage & recycle construction and demolition waste
news.para: Absence of effective rules currently leads to unauthorised dumping due to lack of space for disposal, and improper mixing with biodegradable waste.

news.title: Residents in Jaipur seek compensation after JDA demolished 80% of their properties
news.para: The Congress govt compulsorily acquired their farmlands to establish the nearby army cantonment, and now the BJP govt was demolishing more than 80% of their residential properties to expand Sirsi Road.

news.title: NBCC e-auctions residential units at Aspire Dream Valley for ₹1,504.69 crore
news.para: The fund is expected to mitigate the fund requirement of ongoing projects including bank loan payment.

news.title: Qatar Investment Authority eyes stake in Kering's building in Milan: Report
news.para: The potential deal for the Milan property, which Kering acquired less than a year ago for 1.3 billion euros ($1.4 billion), comes as the luxury conglomerate faces increasing financial pressure due to plummeting sales at its flagship brand Gucci.

news.title: Gurugram: Councillors urge MCG to recover funds from builders for deficient infrastructure in colonies
news.para: While the corporation took over eight private colonies in 2022 as directed by the department of town and country planning (DTCP), it is yet to collect funds from developers to build deficient infrastructure.

news.title: ED raids Noida-based builder in Rs 40 crore money laundering case
news.para: The ED probe stems from about 40 police FIRs filed against the company and its promoters by the investors who allegedly did not get their homes as promised.

news.title: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout site allottees in Bengaluru demand compensation for infra woes
news.para: Tensions ran high at a K-RERA hearing as the site owners, frustrated by prolonged delays, demanded compensation, while BDA struggled to put up a cohesive defence.
